<!doctype html><html><head> <%- include("headElement") %> <title>Create Account</title></head><body> <%- include("header") %> <div class="container"><h2>Create Account</h2><p class="lead">Already have an account? <a href="/createAccount">Log in</a>.</p><form id="create-account-form" method="post" action="/createAccount"><div class="form-group"> <% if (typeof error !== 'undefined' && error.type === "username") { %> <h4 class="text-warning"><%= error.message %></h4> <% } %> <label for="create-username" class="lead">Username</label> <input name="username" class="form-control" aria-describedby="login-username" value="<%= typeof username !== 'undefined' ? username : '' %>"/><p class="form-text">Username must contain 3-20 characters. Letters, numbers, and <code>.!@#$%^&*()_+-=</code> are allowed. Spaces are allowed, but not at the beginning or end.</p></div><div class="form-group"> <% if (typeof error !== 'undefined' && error.type === "password") { %> <h6 class="text-warning"><%= error.message %> <% } %> <label for="create-password" class="lead">Passphrase</label> <input type="password" name="password" class="form-control" aria-describedby="login-password" required/><p class="form-text">Must be between 12 and 99 characters and please <strong class="text-danger">do NOT use anything you have used on another site</strong>.<br/>No, really. I am just a college student who made this as a summer project. I probably have a security hole somewhere. Your best recourse is simply to pick a unique passphrase.</p></h6></div><div class="form-group"> <% if (typeof error !== 'undefined' && error.type === "confirmPassword") { %> <h6 class="text-warning"><%= error.message %> <% } %> <label for="create-confirm-password" class="lead">Confirm Passphrase</label> <input type="password" name="confirmPassword" class="form-control" aria-describedby="login-password" required/><p class="form-text">I really mean it. <strong class="text-warning">DO. NOT. REUSE. PASSWORDS.</strong> (You really should not be reusing them at all, but especially not on some security novice's random project. You might want to look into password managers.)</p></h6></div><p>Note that there is currently no way to reset your password if you forget.</p><input type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg"/></form></div> <%- include("footer") %> <script src="/scripts/vendor.js?0614285fbc14a0987986"></script></body></html>